curam.util.xml.impl

Class XMLDocument

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.xml.impl.XMLDocument

  • public class XMLDocument
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is responsible for maintaining a representation of an XML document.

      • addFromXML

        public void addFromXML(java.lang.String xmlFragment)
                throws AppRuntimeException
        Directly add an XML fragment to the document. It is the responsibility of the client to ensure this fragment matches the relevant parts of the document type definition described in the XML Guide.
        Parameters:
        xmlFragment - A string containing the XML fragment that could have been built up through the normal document APIs. An example of a fragment is 
         
  <STRUCT>
    <SNAME>DWPNotificEvidDtls</SNAME>
    <FIELD>
      <FNAME>bankAccountAmt</FNAME>
      <TYPE>SVR_MONEY</TYPE>
      <VALUE>0.00</VALUE>
    </FIELD>
    <FIELD>
      <FNAME&gtbuildingSocietyAmt&lt;/FNAME>
      <TYPE>SVR_MONEY</TYPE>
      <VALUE>0.00</VALUE>
    </FIELD>
  </STRUCT>
        Throws:
        AppRuntimeException - RUN_ID_RUNTIME- Generic signature that nests any IOException.
        See Also:
        XMLDocument.add(Object)
